This project is a result of several years of collaboration between the partners organizations and other institutions, under the network École des Écoles. EdE addresses mainly practice based research workshops for teachers and teachers’ debate – lifelong learning. This previous activity assures therefore the internal coherence and mutual knowledge of the partners organizations and their importance in European theatre higher education context, the assumptions on which this project lays, the commitment to cross-border cooperation and collaborative learning, the pertinence of a particular set of needs and objectives, the enhancing of skills and competences.

The objectives of the project are related to the modernization of European performing arts / theatre higher education, namely through activities that explore and debate the pedagogical, creative, and managerial potential of an entrepreneurial approach in arts and theatre higher education. Implicit to these objectives are conspicuous changes in the professional context of performing arts, characterized by new configurations of employability that demand new skills and competences, hence new methodologies in training and teaching. The increasingly necessity of building up an autonomous, transnational and flexible artistic career criss-crosses itself with new ways of making theatre, new forms of theatre displaying modes and practices. Schools should address these needs and work as the first platforms for education and professional sustainability, fulfilling their social dimension 
These are the general motives that congregate the partner organizations that will develop and implement specific activities along this two  years project, being Instituto Politécnico de Lisboa - Escola Superior de Teatro e Cinema (IPL-ESTC) the leading partner. The methodology underlying these activities is clear and its main core consists in practice-based research in the ideology of the project and collaborative learning, in planning, observing and exchanging practices of teaching/learning and training in an entrepreneurial context, in developing and practicing mentoring and coaching skills.  These will be implemented through intensive programmes for staff and students, with international classes and seminars /workshops, described here as Learning/teaching/training activities, and intensive research activity, responsibility of the artistic research and steering group, resulting in intellectual outputs for future impact and transference.
 
It is also of particular significance the position and history of Prima del Teatro, the only participating organization that is not a formal school, having, though, an already experienced structure of cross learning, collaborative creation, civil community impact and international teaching in an integrated learning environment.
   
Being a project in the context of European higher education, partner organizations acknowledge and aim for high results in terms of quality standards and impact factors. In what regards to quality standards, functioning as ‘other organization’, EdE supplies a broader context of expertise and dissemination capability to and with other institutions, teachers and professionals, that otherwise would be almost unaware of the project and its activities, fulfilling at the same time an important function of assessment. EdE network multiplies therefore the impact of this project’s activities, outputs and results. This necessarily means that the project expects results in four basic domains:
- the domain of teaching and learning process and methodologies, promoting, exploring and testing a creative, collaborative, problem-based pedagogical environment;
-  the domain of knowledge producing and exchanging of good practices, through intellectual outputs and guidelines;
- the domain of developing skills and competences, understood as urgent answers to new configurations of art and theatre productions and to the demands of the professional market;
- the domain of curricula development and curricula by-products, including the debate about theatre higher education and digital means of teaching, learning and art / theatre producing.
